nl_problem:
# Task: Nested Logic Test (Depth 15)
# Interface:
Class: Solution
Method: checkNested(self, x0: int, x1: int, x2: int, x3: int, x4: int, x5: int, x6: int, x7: int, x8: int, x9: int, x10: int, x11: int, x12: int, x13: int, x14: int) -> bool

# Objective:
This is a test of structural nesting. Return True ONLY if all the following conditions are met:
1. x0 is greater than 0
2. x1 is greater than 0
3. x2 is greater than 0
4. x3 is greater than 0
5. x4 is greater than 0
6. x5 is greater than 0
7. x6 is greater than 0
8. x7 is greater than 0
9. x8 is greater than 0
10. x9 is greater than 0
11. x10 is greater than 0
12. x11 is greater than 0
13. x12 is greater than 0
14. x13 is greater than 0
15. x14 is greater than 0

Each condition must be checked inside the previous one (nested if statements).
lisp_spec:
(task
  (name "checkNested")
  (signature ((x0 int) (x1 int) (x2 int) (x3 int) (x4 int) (x5 int) (x6 int) (x7 int) (x8 int) (x9 int) (x10 int) (x11 int) (x12 int) (x13 int) (x14 int)) bool)
  (constraints
    (constraint "All input parameters must be integers.")
    (constraint "The function should return a boolean value indicating whether all conditions are met or not.")
  )
  (goal
    (description "Check if all the given integer inputs x0 to x14 are greater than 0, with each condition nested within the previous one. Return True only if all conditions are satisfied.")
    (rule "The function should perform a series of nested conditional checks on the input parameters.")
    (return "Returns true if all input integers from x0 to x14 are greater than 0; otherwise, returns false.")
  )
)
